<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DCM AND DDM DRUM TYPE PARKING BRAKE - BENDIX DUO DUTY MECHANICAL BRAKE - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <para>Before assembly, apply a thin layer of Fleetrite EP2 Moly Grease or equivalent NLGI #2 Multi-purpose
            lithium grease to the following parts:
        </para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Camshaft lugs and ball.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Support plate shoe-guide lugs and shoe bearing surfaces.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Support plate anchor pins.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Contact surfaces at both ends of the shoe web. Use caution to keep lubricant off the linings.
                </para>
                <para>Apply a light coating of NLGI Grade No. 2 lithium grease to all clevis pins.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Use only a light coating of grease at points specified. Excess grease can melt from brake heat and
                    drip on drum and lining surfaces. This will cause reduced brake performance.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
